  "title": "Module 1 Roadmap",
  "body": " Module 1 Roadmap   All of the content in this module should be completed before class on Wednesday, July 1 .    The Big Picture  If we're going to spend an entire semester talking about differential equations, we should probably start with what differential equations are to begin with. In this module, we will define differential equations and establish some vocabulary to help us describe and classify them. We will also see some real-world problems that can be modeled with differential equations to hopefully build motivation to study them.    Module Objectives  After progressing through this module, students will be able to...  Determine the order of differential equations.  Determine the linearity of differential equations.  Verify solutions to differential equations.  Find the interval of existance for solutions to differential equations.  Model simple real-world phenomena with first-order initial value problems.      To Do List  In this module, you will...  Watch TBD videos (runtimes here)  Complete TBD checkpoints  Update your prep work journal.  Complete all assigned problems in Homework 1 .  Complete Activity 0 (this would be last-week's activity if there was one).      "
