  "body": " Activity 1     Instructions: Write solutions to each of the following problems in the space provided. You are encouraged to work in groups, but also encouraged to use your own words to express your ideas.       Go to the Wikipedia entry entitled \"List of Named Differential Equations\". For each of the following categories, chose and write down a differential equation that stands out to you and one listed application for it. Identify the equations order, then state whether it is ordinary or partial. If it is ordinary, determine whether it is linear.     Math      Physics      Engineering      Chemistry      Biology and medicine      Economics and finance         For each of the following, write an initial value problem to model the scenario.      Population growth: The culture was seeded with 500 bacteria, whose population growth rate at time grew proportionally to its population.       Harmonic Oscillator: A mass kg is attached to a spring and hung from the ceiling. The spring is stretched by meters from its equilibrium position and is let go, setting the system in (bouncy, springy) motion. Let denote the spring's position at time .        Solar Collector: A solar collector is shaped like the solid generated by revolving the curve about the -axis. Its purpose is to reflect all light light rays parallel to its axis of symmetry to the same point (the origin). The Law of reflection tells us that the angle of incedence and reflection are equal. Write a differential equation that describes the shape of .     Try showing the the angle the reflected ray makes with respect to the -axis is exactly twice the angle the tangent line to makes with respect to the axis.     "
